<exercise checkit-seed="0001" checkit-slug="M3" checkit-title="Invertible matrices">
  <statement>
      <p>Explain why the matrix <m>P=\left[\begin{array}{cccc}
-3 &amp; -1 &amp; 7 &amp; 4 \\
-3 &amp; -5 &amp; -1 &amp; -4 \\
4 &amp; 3 &amp; -6 &amp; -2 \\
-1 &amp; -1 &amp; 1 &amp; 0
\end{array}\right]</m> is or is not invertible.</p>
  </statement>
  <answer>
      <p><me>\mathrm{RREF}\,\left[\begin{array}{cccc}
-3 &amp; -1 &amp; 7 &amp; 4 \\
-3 &amp; -5 &amp; -1 &amp; -4 \\
4 &amp; 3 &amp; -6 &amp; -2 \\
-1 &amp; -1 &amp; 1 &amp; 0
\end{array}\right]=\left[\begin{array}{cccc}
1 &amp; 0 &amp; -3 &amp; -2 \\
0 &amp; 1 &amp; 2 &amp; 2 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0
\end{array}\right]</me></p>
      <p><m>P</m> is not  invertible.</p>
  </answer>
</exercise>
